              "raw": "{\r\n  \"title\": \"Design UI\",\r\n  \"description\": \"Create wireframes\",\r\n  \"status\": \"todo\",\r\n  \"priority\": \"high\",\r\n  \"due_date\": \"2026-04-20\"\r\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:3000/projects/69dde8542b75d848482182d5/tasks",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "localhost"
              ],
              "port": "3000",
              "path": [
                "projects",
                "69dde8542b75d848482182d5",
                "tasks"
              ]
            },
            "description": "## Create Task\n\nCreates a new task under a specific project.\n\n### Endpoint\n\n`POST /projects/:projectId/tasks`\n\n### Request Body\n\nSend a JSON object with the following fields:\n\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `title` | string | Yes | The title of the task (e.g. `\"Design UI\"`) |\n| `description` | string | No | A brief description of the task (e.g. `\"Create wireframes\"`) |\n| `status` | string | No | Current status of the task. Possible values: `\"todo\"` |\n| `priority` | string | No | Priority level of the task. Possible values: `\"high\"` |\n| `due_date` | string (ISO 8601) | No | The due date for the task in `YYYY-MM-DD` format (e.g. `\"2026-04-20\"`) |\n\n### Example Request Body\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"title\": \"Design UI\",\n  \"description\": \"Create wireframes\",\n  \"status\": \"todo\",\n  \"priority\": \"high\",\n  \"due_date\": \"2026-04-20\"\n}\n\n ```\n\n### Notes\n\n- The `projectId` in the URL path must be a valid project ID.\n    \n- The `due_date` should follow the `YYYY-MM-DD` format."
          },
          "response": []
        },
